physdesc.extent: 228 manuscript boxes, 1 oversize box, 31 envelopes, 11 sound cassettes, 4 sound discs

did.abstract: Correspondence, memoranda, reports, notes, press releases, press conference transcripts, press summaries, photographs, clippings, and other printed matter relating to American foreign and domestic policy during the presidential administrations of Richard M. Nixon and Gerald R. Ford, the Watergate affair, and the American press. Digital copies of select records also available at https://digitalcollections.hoover.org.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research. Digital copies of select records also available at https://digitalcollections.hoover.org.

The Hoover Institution Archives only allows access to copies of audiovisual items, computer media, and digital files. To listen to sound recordings or to view videos, films, or digital files during your visit, please contact the Archives at least two working days before your arrival. We will then advise you of the accessibility of the material you wish to see or hear. Please note that not all material is immediately accessible.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: For copyright status, please contact the Hoover Institution Archives.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Gerald Lee Warren papers, [Box no.], Hoover Institution Archives.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Materials were acquired by the Hoover Institution Archives in 1980, with an increment received in 1995.

accruals.head: Accruals
accruals.p: Materials may have been added to the collection since this finding aid was prepared. To determine if this has occurred, find the collection in Stanford University's online catalog at http://searchworks.stanford.edu/. Materials have been added to the collection if the number of boxes listed in the online catalog is larger than the number of boxes listed in this finding aid.

altformavail.head: Alternate Forms Available
altformavail.p: Digital copies of select records also available at https://digitalcollections.hoover.org.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content of Collection
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, memoranda, reports, notes, press releases, press conference transcripts, press summaries, photographs, clippings, and other printed matter relating to American foreign and domestic policy during the presidential administrations of Richard M. Nixon and Gerald R. Ford, the Watergate affair, and the American press.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Clippings, correspondence, curriculum vitae, and memoranda relating to the life of Gerald Warren and his alma mater, University of Nebraska, arranged in alphabetical order by physical form.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Brochures, clippings, correspondence, holograph notes, memoranda, newsletters, outlines of speeches, press releases, printed matter, schedules, and telegrams, arranged in chronological order.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Appointment diaries, clippings, correspondence, daily files including holograph notes, interviews, invitations, meetings, memoranda, newsletters, press briefings, press conferences, press releases, printed matter, remarks, schedules, statements, telegrams, television reports, and travel itineraries of Gerald Warren, arranged in alphabetical order by physical form. Includes Gerald Warren's resignation from the White House press office under President Gerald Ford.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Brochures, bulletins, correspondence, executive orders, interviews, meetings, memoranda, messages to Congress, newsletters, news summaries, pool reports, press briefings, press conferences, press releases, printed matter, proclamations, remarks, reports, schedules, statements, telegrams, television news reports, testimonies, and travel itineraries, both domestic and foreign, relating to President Nixon and President Ford, their press offices, cabinet and other government officials, and papers relating to President Nixon's personal financial situation, arranged alphabetically by physical form.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Brochures, correspondence, executive orders, interviews, meetings, memoranda, messages, newsletters, news summaries, pool reports, press briefings, press conferences, press releases, printed matter, proclamations, remarks, schedules, statements, telegrams, and television news reports relating to the cabinet, Congress, guidelines for declassifying government papers, domestic programs, United States relations with foreign nations, issues involving foreign aid and foreign trade, American prisoners of war and Americans missing in action, interaction between the White House and the media, the Republican party and the elections, state of the union messages, the plans of reorganizing the administrative structure of the White House and the federal government, presidential appointees and the rules of conduct for the White House staff, President Nixon's inauguration, his health, and the controversy surrounding the Watergate break-in, arranged alphabetically by physical form.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Brochures, bulletins, correspondence, editorials, meetings, memoranda, newsletters, news summaries, press releases, printed matter, remarks and reports relating to Gerald Warren's connections with the San Diego Union during his years at the White House and to the later publication of the newspaper under his direction as editor, arranged alphabetically by physical form.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, executive orders, fact sheets, interviews, memoranda, press releases, proclamations, remarks, schedules, statements, and telegrams relating to the accomplishments of Richard Nixon and Gerald Ford as presidents, the first families, Mrs. Nixon's trips abroad as personal representative of the president, the presidential retreat of Camp David, the funerals of ex-presidents Eisenhower, Truman, and Johnson, speeches and writings by government officials and others, and the departure of president Richard Nixon from the White House following his resignation, arranged in alphabetical order.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Nixon-related materials, consisting of a memorandum for the President (7 December 1970), paper on "White House Communications Leadership Responsibilities" (25 March 1971), card of voice call signs from the White House Communications Agency (August 1974), a photo of Nixon on his 75th birthday (9 January 1988), a letter from Nixon to Warren (8 March 1988), and a newspaper article on the occasion of Nixon's death (24 April 1994).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Formerly security-classified records of the U.S. government, released in full or in part. Includes some interfiled, unclassified government records. Arranged chronologically by date of release by Hoover, thereunder chronologically by date of creation.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Telegrams, memoranda, and newspaper clipping, often from the Secretary of State or Department of Defense, relating to military and political situations and U.S. foreign policy in Laos, Vietnam, Chile, and the Middle East.
